LOCAL TITLE: MENTAL HEALTH PRRC INDIVIDUAL NOTE                 
STANDARD TITLE: MENTAL HEALTH NOTE                              
DATE OF NOTE: NOV 10, 2025@12:21     ENTRY DATE: NOV 10, 2025@12:21:07      
      AUTHOR: PIERCE,RENEE D       EXP COSIGNER:                           
     URGENCY:                            STATUS: COMPLETED                     


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVT. Appointment was conducted via tele-mental health/clinical video 
teleconferencing (CVT).

Veteran has been informed of and verbally consented to the following:
1. The nature of tele-mental health and its benefits and risks 
2. Confidentiality and its limits 
3. The emergency plan (see below for details) 

EMERGENCY PLAN 
In the event of an emergency, provider may: 
- As available (e.g., CBOC, shelter) and appropriate, attempt to alert on-
site
staff to the situation so that they can initiate the existing on-site 
emergency
protocol. 
- Call e911 at 267-908-6605 and ask to be connected to emergency services for
the location of the emergency. 

Veterans location for this appointment (verified with Veteran): 
Non-VA location type: [e.g., home, shelter, work, vehicle] 
Patient's location address: 
              SCOTT WELDON ODELL
      3610 33RD AVE S APT A310
      SEATTLE,WA  98144 
        Patient's Residence Phone No.: (206) 293-9433 
        Patient E-Mail Address: SCOTT.ODELL12345@GMAIL.COM 
Providers location and contact information for this appointment (verified 
with
Veteran): 
Providers location: Seattle VA, Building 101 
Providers phone: (206) 277- 4384 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_______________________________________________________________________ 
          PSYCHOSOCIAL REHABILITATION & RECOVERY CENTER (PRRC) 
                             INDIVIDUAL NOTE 
________________________________________________________________________

DIAGNOSES TREATED DURING THIS VISIT:
 Chronic PTSD. Anxiety. Depression. 

RECOVERY GOAL ADDRESSED TODAY:
  "Learn how to manage my symptoms of or PTSD and depression and be in the
  present moment to keep myself from  thinking ahead and worrying about
  unnecessary  things far  in the future that I don't have control over."


SIGNIFICANT SYMPTOMS/ISSUES DISCUSSED:
Scott Odell, a 68yo, 100% SC(70%PTSD), Post-Vietnam Era Veteran, with history of 
PTSD and depression , presented to scheduled monthly PRRC  VVC individual 
recovery coaching session on time with anxious mood and congruent affect. 
Veteran was ecstatic to share that his service connected disability application 
was increase to 100%SC.  Vet also shared that he has been sic the oast few days. 
Reports he went to SVA for nasal swab test however was informed he was negative 
for COVID and for the flu. Reports continues to have cold and fever sxs. Reports 
in communication with PCP and plans to go to PCP for chest xray once he has more 
energy.  Vet denied any other major concerns or needs, expressed. appreciation 
for support and agreed to meet for next RC session in 4 weeks.


MENTAL STATUS EXAMINATION:
  BEHAVIOR:
    Cooperative

  ORIENTATION AND CONSCIOUSNESS:
    Alert and attentive
    Oriented X 3

  COGNITIVE FUNCTIONING:
    Memory, concentration and attention are unimpaired

  SPEECH:
    Coherent
    Normal rate and rhythm

  AFFECT:
    Congruant w/ mood 

  MOOD:
    Stable

  PERCEPTUAL DISTURBANCE:
    No hallucinations voiced during this session.

  THOUGHT PROCESS AND ASSOCIATION:
    Linear and goal directed
    No impairment of thought process

  THOUGHT CONTENT:
    No delusions voiced during this session. 

  INSIGHT AND JUDGMENT:
    Awareness of disorder(s)
    Good judgment about current life decisions

BRIEF ASSESSMENT OF CURRENT RISK:
  Veteran was specifically asked about and denied suicidal ideation 
since last visit. 
  Veteran was specifically asked about and denied ideation to physically 
    harm others since last visit.

PROTECTIVE FACTORS:

  Itemized Protective Factors:
    Active participation in treatment/positive therapeutic relationship
    Positive social support
    Positive coping skills
    Problem solving skills
    Plans and/or hopes for future

PLAN:
(1) Attend monthly  PRRC  Recovery Coaching Sessions. 
        - RTC 12/08 @11am 

(2) Attend Med provider sessions, as scheduled

(3) Weekly Therapy  Groups:  on hiatus, per vet request 
        - Groups Completed: 
                - Emotion Regulation Group, Summer 2020
                - Mindfulness Core Skills Group, Fall 19 
                - Anxiety Self-Man

(4) Vet to pursue VA SC claim appeal for neropothy with VSO assistance 
 
 
/es/ Renee D. Pierce,
Clinical Social Worker
Signed: 11/10/2025 12:59
